caption.center: DAVID M. WILLIAMS, Defendant Below, Appellant, v. STATE OF DELAWARE,

opinion.posture: Court Below: Superior Court of the State of Delaware in and for New Castle County, Cr. ID No. 9803018202B.
opinion.opinion_text:
This 14TH day of February 2008, it appears to the Court that:
(1) The Order dated January 23, 2008 in this case was issued in error and is hereby WITHDRAWN.
(2) On December 18, 2007, the Senior Court Clerk issued a notice to show cause why this appeal should not be dismissed, pursuant to Supreme Court Rule 29(b), based on this Court's lack of jurisdiction to entertain an appeal from a decision that was not a final order. The appellant has failed to respond to the notice to show cause within the required ten-day period; therefore, dismissal of this action is deemed to be unopposed.
NOW, THEREFORE, IT IS HEREBY ORDERED, pursuant to Supreme Court Rules 3(b) and 29(b), that the within appeal is DISMISSED.Page 1
